quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"Say: 'What, though I should bring you a better guidance than you found your fathers upon?' They say, 'We disbelieve in that you were sent with"
  43,25,So We took vengeance upon them; and behold how was the end of them that cried lies
  43,26,"And when Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Surely I am quit of that you serve"
  43,27,except Him who originated me; and He will guide me
  43,28,And he made it a word enduring among his posterity; haply so they would return
  43,29,"Nay, but I gave these and their fathers enjoyment of days, until the truth came unto them, and a manifest Messenger"
  43,30,"And when the truth came to them, they said, 'This is a sorcery, and in it we are unbelievers"
  43,31,"They say, 'Why was this Koran not sent down upon some man of moment in the two cities"
  43,32,"What, is it they who divide the mercy of the Lord? We have divided between them their livelihood in the present life, and raised some of them above others in rank, that some of them may take others in servitude; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than that they amass"
  43,33,"And were it not that mankind would be one nation, We would have appointed for those who disbelieve in the All-merciful roofs of silver to their houses, and stairs whereon to mount"
  43,34,"and doors to their houses, and couches whereon to recline"
  43,35,"and ornaments; surely all this is but the enjoyment of the present life, and the world to come with thy Lord is for the godfearing"
  43,36,"Whoso blinds himself to the Remembrance of the All-merciful, to him We assign a Satan for comrade"
  43,37,"and they bar them from the way, and they think they are guided"
  43,38,"till, when he comes to Us, he says, 'Would there had been between me and thee the distance of the two Easts!' An evil comrade"
  43,39,"It shall not profit you today, since you did evil, that you are partners in the chastisement"
  43,40,"What, shalt thou make the deaf to hear, or shalt thou guide the blind and him who is in manifest error"
  43,41,"Whether We take thee away, We shall take vengeance upon them"
  43,42,"or We show thee a part of that We promised them, surely We have power over them"
  43,43,So hold thou fast unto that which has been revealed unto thee; surely thou art upon a straight path
  43,44,Surely it is a Reminder to thee and to thy people; and assuredly you will be questioned
  43,45,"Ask those of Our Messengers We sent before thee: Have We appointed, apart from the All-merciful, gods to be served"
  43,46,"We also sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his Council, and he said, 'Surely, I am the Messenger of the Lord of all Being"
  43,47,"But when he brought them Our signs, lo, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"And not a sign We showed them, but it was greater than its sister sign; and We seized them with chastisement, that haply they should return"
  43,49,"And they said, 'Sorcerer, pray to thy Lord for us by the covenant He has made with thee, and surely we shall be right-guided"
  43,50,"But when We removed from them the chastisement, behold, they broke their troth"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed among his people: 'O my people, do I not possess the kingdom of Egypt, and these rivers flowing beneath me? What, do you not see"
  43,52,"Or am I better than this man, who is contemptible and scarcely makes things clear"
  43,53,"Why then have bracelets of gold not been cast on him, or angels not come with him conjoined"
  43,54,"So he made his people unsteady, and they obeyed him; surely they were an ungodly people"
  43,55,"So, when they had angered Us, We took vengeance on them, and We drowned them all together"
  43,56,"and We made them a thing past, and We appointed them for an example to later folk"